column1: Tomorrow our bipartisan Congressional Women’s Caucus and The @PlzSolveCFS Initiative will host a virtual roundtable to discuss chronic illness during the time of #COVID19.  Register through this link to attend: https://t.co/ppuaRUHLbs. #MEcfs https://t.co/JEK73ijMre

Join me for a webinar with @CMSGov representatives to learn about the changes and updates the agency has made in response to the #COVID_19 pandemic. It will be this Thursday June 18 at 10:00am.  Make sure to register here: https://t.co/7yisoyx2Le https://t.co/QyRGTGYnDI

Earlier today my @NewDemCoalition colleagues and I had a call with Dr. Fauci who shared his insights and perspectives on the coronavirus pandemic.  We are all incredibly grateful for his expertise and guidance.  @NIAIDNews

We are grateful for the work of law enforcement officers who protect our communities and our families.  This year in particular I honor the brave sacrifices of first responders who risk exposure to #COVID-19 in their daily line of work. #PoliceWeek https://t.co/J19I1T4cQx

The daily routines of millions have been disrupted by the #COVID19 pandemic.  You're invited to join me the @AtlantaVAMC & the @ALZAssociation TOMORROW for a conversation about veterans’ mental health & resources available for caretakers.  To register: https://t.co/0WhrkP1iOO https://t.co/NcsIGpgAV2

REMINDER: Join us tomorrow afternoon for a Social Security COVID-19 Update.   If you'd like to submit a question for the @SocialSecurity Administration please do so by 5:00pm tonight through this registration form.   https://t.co/mddOM4h5AG https://t.co/F8hYJS5zPw

I’m hosting another Small Business webinar this afternoon at 1pm for owners & managers to learn more about #COVIDー19 federal resources.  We’ll hear from experts from the @ugasbdc & the @GABankers. Please register here to receive the call information. https://t.co/CPTS9Nzenc https://t.co/I3rxlif8cB

I’m hosting a webinar tomorrow for business owners & managers to learn more about #COVIDー19 federal resources.  We’ll hear from experts from the @ugasbdc and the @GeorgiaTech Enterprise Innovation Institute. Please register for the event here: https://t.co/0AV7sh5hcq https://t.co/8AqC2eCXhD

No one should feel unsafe in their own home.  During #COVID19 when we’re all doing our part by staying in we must protect those most vulnerable to domestic violence.  The Senate should join us in reauthorizing #VAWA and standing up against violence.

I’m hosting another #Coronavirus Telephone Town Hall tomorrow April 2 at 7:30pm.  I’ll be joined by experts to answer your questions about #COVID19 and options for small businesses.  Register to receive a call when it begins by visiting https://t.co/5GtaMIplqI. https://t.co/nsXEyskrLm

This toolkit can help you understand all the Constituent Services & benefits that are available under the new #COVID_19 packages — and how you can access them.  https://t.co/23svNPSrua https://t.co/MQAT5VtyEq

BREAKING: The House just passed the bipartisan CARES Act. I’m proud to support this bill & give #COVID19 emergency relief to American families workers and businesses.  Read my full statement & learn more about this package. https://t.co/xKV1Wibuum
Make sure you have the facts about #COVIDー19 from @FEMA. https://t.co/KsAVk5deog https://t.co/obDhifzwnb

The @RedCross is facing a shortage because of blood drive cancellations during the #COVID19 crisis. Many patients rely on transfusions & donating is an important step toward saving a life.  For health facts & to find ways to help visit https://t.co/x7Q0YCIHoZ.
REMINDER: Our Telephone Town Hall on the #COVID-19 coronavirus begins in 15 minutes.  To register and receive a call visit https://t.co/5GtaMI7K28. https://t.co/5gbrovoWRQ

Because of a statewide disaster declaration from the @SBAgov applications are now available for emergency loans to small businesses & nonprofit organizations impacted by #COVID19.  Visit https://t.co/AmvKGaRZVI for more information & to apply.

To help make sure we all have the most up-to-date & accurate information on #coronavirus I’m holding a telephone Town Hall tomorrow March 20th at 7:00pm.  Register at https://t.co/5GtaMIplqI to receive a phone call when the event is beginning. https://t.co/1B4n5Ge4SR

We must all come together and do our part to help keep each other safe.  My Public Service Announcement with the @WeatherChannel highlights the simple everyday actions we can take to help prevent the spread of the COVID-19 coronavirus. https://t.co/s1DBygOxXx
The State of Georgia has a new #COVID19 hotline.  Call (844) 442-2681 to ask a question hear what to do if you feel ill or be connected with the @GaDPH.

This bipartisan bill makes #COVID19 coronavirus tests free to everyone who needs one supports workers who should stay home to keep people healthy and makes sure children & seniors have access to the food they need.  I was proud to vote YES & to pass it.  https://t.co/5IfxL8dZDJ

The Georgia Department of Public Health is providing daily updates on #COVID19 in the state.  You can find additional #GA06 county & city specific resources on my website: https://t.co/OddI7i72AH https://t.co/vPMPXJGh7f

I want to extend my deepest prayers and condolences to the family and friends of the individual who passed from the Coronavirus.  As we continue to address this pandemic we must work together to prevent its spread and keep our families safe and healthy. https://t.co/qSTINIr2l5

To help keep people safe & healthy during the COVID-19 outbreak I've co-sponsored:  • Paid sick days for low-wage workers • No-cost coronavirus testing • Plans to ensure kids continue receiving affordable meals if their schools close  For resources visit my website. https://t.co/F1YteNmKHj
We're closely monitoring #COVID19 and working with our state & local partners.  For resources and ways to protect yourself & your loved ones visit my website ⬇️ https://t.co/lYLTqT4aws

We're closely monitoring #COVID19. Here are a few ways to protect yourself & loved ones:  • Cover your cough or sneeze w/ a tissue then throw the tissue in the trash  • Wash your hands often with soap & water for 20+ secs  • Avoid touching your eyes nose & mouth https://t.co/cH9P8OuW5w
